\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that all minimum standards have been met. Where a need of improvement is indicated\'2C it is based on data provided by the institution that appears to be inconsistent and in need of verification.\line \line Overall the evaluator is satisfied with the programme design\'2C since the number of credits per module has been more clearly explained in subsequent documentation. The Evaluator noted that there are no specified pre-requisite credits indicated for the Level 6 Module included in the programme. The inclusion of a level 6 module needs to be clarified and if it is correct\'2C it should be indicated if any specific pre-requisites will be set for the module. \line \line The evaluator also noted that in terms of Criterion 7\'2C no budget specifically for this programme had been supplied. The budget which appears in the documentation is for the entire Institution. There should be programme specific budgets attached to the application. Furthermore the Institution needs to check and change the wording regarding the number of cameras available. The documentation reads \'E2\'80\'98\'E2\'80\'A68 broadcast cameras per student\'E2\'80\'A6\'E2\'80\'99 The evaluator understands that this is a textual error\'2C and assumes it should read \'E2\'80\'98\'E2\'80\'A68 students per broadcast camera\'E2\'80\'A6\'E2\'80\'99 If this is not the case it would be both highly unusual and also need further explanation. \line \line \line The evaluator indicated that there does not seem to be any access to television studios. The documentation states \'E2\'80\'98Rental of facilities from SABC means facilities can be adapted easily to suit needs of screen media\'E2\'80\'99 \'287.1 pgs 46 and 47\'29. However\'2C the evaluator is not sure what this implies. \line \line The Directorate supports the recommendation that the programme should be accredited with conditions.\line \line \cell \pard 

